- `OidcFacade` is the OidcFacade from the module

The initializer is defined as:

```
function initApp(configService: AppConfigService, config: Config, oidcFacade: OidcFacade) {
    return (): Promise&lt;any&gt; =&gt; {
      return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
        configService.loadAppConfig()
          .then((cfg) =&gt; {
            setOidcConfig(config, configService.getConfig(), oidcFacade);
          })
          .then(() =&gt; oidcFacade.waitForAuthenticationLoaded().toPromise())
          .then(() =&gt; oidcFacade.loggedIn$.pipe(take(1)).toPromise())
          .then((loggedIn) =&gt; forceLogIn(oidcFacade, loggedIn))
          .then(() =&gt; resolve())
          .catch(error =&gt; reject(error));
      });
    };
}
```

In our case, we force the user to be logged on when the application is loaded via the `forceLogIn` method which issues the `signinRedirect` action if not logged in,  but could be limited to just the config setting if not required.

